            Over the last few years I've used Linux a fair amount. I started using Linux a few years ago
            when I was getting tired of the load of crap that comes with Windows. I also decided that it would
            be cool to use the command line for most of my daily tasks. Admittedly I just wanted to impress my
            friends for the most part. I began with Ubuntu, like the majority of Linux-goers nowadays. Next I
