            laptop has been close to impossible. Even when your hardware is supported, you can still have serious
            problems. I can't tell you how many times I've had to troubleshoot graphics drivers during and after
            installation. I've also had to use PS2 adapters just to boot into Linux, because my USB keyboard wasn't
            supported.
          </p>
          <p>
